My Arduino Project Ideas (all my ideas came from reflecting on them and only used ChaGPT to give structure and to rewrite this neater)
1. Movement Control System

An Arduino program that monitors a person’s movement using sensors and provides feedback with coloured lights and sound.

Green light: The person is staying still, so no message is played.

Red light: Movement is detected, and the system tells the person to stop moving.

Blue light: The system detects too little movement and instructs the person to move more.

This system could be used for training exercises that require controlled movement or stillness.

2. Skill Training Assistant

An Arduino-based training system that helps users learn physical skills by analysing their movement and posture.

Sensors monitor the user’s form and flexibility.

The system gives audio feedback with different sounds depending on performance.

It guides the user through stages of learning a skill (for example, exercises leading up to performing a backflip).

Progress is tracked with a scoring system, and the device congratulates users when they reach new milestones.

The program could be updated over time with new skills and training programs.

3. Movement Boundary Trainer

A system that tracks whether a person stays within a defined training area.

Sensors detect when a foot steps outside a marked zone.

If the user leaves the zone, the movement does not count toward the exercise.

The goal is to help users learn proper form and positioning during training.

4. Stress Detection and Relaxation Assistant

An Arduino device that monitors a person's stress level using sensors such as heart rate or skin conductivity.

Depending on the detected stress level, the system suggests ways to relax, such as:

Taking a walk outdoors

Listening to calming music

Eating or drinking something relaxing

The device could also play different songs or sounds to help reduce stress.

5. Automatic Training Timer

A timing system that automatically records performance during training.

A sensor detects when a person crosses a start line and starts the timer.

When the line is crossed again, the timer stops automatically.

Green light: A new personal record is achieved.

Red flashing light: The new time is faster than the previous attempt but not a record.

This makes training sessions more engaging and competitive.

6. Nose-Breathing Reminder

A wearable Arduino device designed to encourage nose breathing instead of mouth breathing.

Sensors detect when the user opens their mouth.

If mouth breathing occurs, the device sends a reminder signal (sound or vibration).

The goal is to reinforce healthy breathing habits.

7. Energy Drink and Blood Pressure Tracker

An Arduino system that measures how different energy drinks affect blood pressure.

The device records blood pressure after consuming different drinks.

It keeps track of which drink gives the user better energy with lower blood pressure.

Based on the data, the system could recommend the most suitable caffeinated drink.

8. Emotion Regulation Device

A device that detects signs of anger or emotional stress.

When the system detects an angry mood, it responds by:

Playing calming music (such as a lullaby)

Sending gentle vibration alerts to encourage the user to calm down

The goal is to help users regain emotional control.

9. Facial Symmetry and Habit Correction System

A system that analyses facial symmetry using sensors or a camera.

It tracks habits that may affect facial balance, such as sleeping position or chewing patterns.

The device suggests:

Which side to sleep on

Which side of the jaw to chew with

Over time, it could expand to help correct other posture or habit-related issues.

10. Adjustable Smart Tint Glasses

Smart glasses with a tint level that can be adjusted manually.

Sliding your fingers across the frame changes the darkness of the lenses.

This allows quick adjustment depending on lighting conditions.

11. Phone Usage Reminder

An Arduino wearable device that helps reduce unnecessary phone use.

When the system detects that the user has been using their phone for more than 10 seconds without searching for something necessary, it sends small vibration alerts.

This reminds the user to stop unnecessary scrolling.
